          "date": "2013-01-25 19:31:40.000000000",
          "tz": -480
        },
        "subject": "LU-2190 mountconf: revert previous commit 8e249d43f19",
        "message": "LU-2190 mountconf: revert previous commit 8e249d43f19\n\nRevert \"LU-2190 mountconf: zfs processes mount parameters\"\n\nThis reverts commit 8e249d43f19a4d227c76e6def41d7eb19e6a207f.\n\nThe reverted patch is incompatible with existing ZFS based file systems,\nand is arguably the wrong approach to take in general. If a single ZFS\ndata set parameter is desired, a patch needs to be written such that it\nis backwards compatible with existing file systems. This will give sites\na \"grace period\" in which they can convert their file systems to use the\nnew configuration format.\n\nWith that said, I'd argue that using a single ZFS dataset parameter for\nthe Lustre configuration parameters makes it much more difficult to\nadminister, and is a regression on its own; regardless of the lack of\nbackwards compatibility.\n\nSigned-off-by: Prakash Surya <surya1@llnl.gov>\nChange-Id: I3a6f005144106966aec0ef18105ce9639cf1f034\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
